    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mi">m</span>
     <span class="mi">m</span>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> is not so small that we can approximate 
  <div id="nlm-math-125" class="math">
   <div class="mrow">
    <div accent="true" class="mover">
     <span class="mi">z</span>
     <span class="mo">¯</span>
    </div>
    <span class="mo">≈</span>
    <span class="mi">θ</span>
   </div>
  </div>, equation 
  <a rid="evo12635-disp-0010" ref-type="disp-formula" href="#evo12635-disp-0010">(8c)</a> also shows that there are trade‐offs between minimizing the phenotypic variance, minimizing the cost of maternal effects, and reaching the optimal phenotype (see Fig. S2).
 </p>
